08/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The ninth session of the Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH)-Croatia Interstate Council for Co-operation took place in Zagreb on Monday (7 June). 
Afterwards, Croatian President Stipe Mesic said that the two countries confirmed their willingness to resolve bilateral problems in the spirit of Euro-Atlantic integration.
In other news, BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic visited Britain on Monday. 
He and British counterpart Geoffrey Hoon discussed BiH's bid for membership in the NATO Partnership for Peace programme and the future role of an EU force in BIH peacekeeping.
Also Monday, Republika Serpska arranged to house the headquarters of the BiH Indirect Taxation Administration in Banja Luka. 
The contractors for the 6.9m-euro project will be the local construction company Vrbas and Nova Banka Bijeljina. 
(Dnevni avaz, RS government Web site, PBS BiH - 07/06/04; HINA, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat - 06/06/04)
